  "finding": "This diagnostic remains valid as a SOTA counterexample for throughput, p50/p95, CPU, and RSS, but its TLS I/O counter interpretation is superseded. Runtime review found that bench_tls_io counters are global; the old single-client worker implementation collected a global delta in each worker and then summed those deltas, inflating SSL_read and pending counts. The corrected dynamic-budget-tlsio-candidate dataset shows the expected stable shape: HTTP-over-HTTPS-proxy averages 2 SSL_read calls and 1 SSL-read pending per request, while HTTPS-origin proxy scenarios average 5 SSL_read calls and 2 SSL-read pendings per request.",
